tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated serum creatinine and low total CO₂, suggesting impaired renal function and possible metabolic acidosis. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glucosuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance, indicating possible nephropathy (e.g., diabetic or other chronic kidney disease). No evidence of urinary tract infection is present. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment of glycemic control.
